✅ Trip Overview cards exclude arrival/departure/Day 0 (Trip Overview.html Arrival / departure days excluded)
✅ Trip Overview — stop count matches day-block stop count for each day (1 overview entry per stop — mismatch means a stop was added/removed without updating the overview card)
✅ Trip Overview — each overview stop entry matches its day-block stop name (substring match in either direction; overview may simplify — mismatch means a stop was renamed without updating the overview card)
✅ Stop description rows (📒) must be ≤320 chars / 4 lines (per Icon Order and Format.html — 📒 Stop description row)
✅ 📒 description must be plain text — no embedded <a> links (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 1 (outside the blue box) — description is text only)
✅ 📒 description must not contain build annotations — [UPDATE]/[CHECK]/🔴/[TBD] etc. must be stripped before shipping (per Icon Order and Format.html § 2 Pos 1 — description is shipped narrative, same rule as stop-name annotation leakage)
✅ No bare hours (use 9:00am, not 9 am)
✅ am/pm must be attached directly to time digits — "9:00am" not "9:00 am"
✅ Time am/pm is lowercase (not AM/PM)
✅ No 24-hour times (use 12-hour format)
✅ 🏛 row format: must match "🏛 Open 24/7", "🏛 Daily {H:MMam} - {H:MMpm}", "🏛 {Weekday}( - {Weekday}) {H:MMam} - {H:MMpm}", or multi-segment "🏛 {segment} · {segment} · …" — closed-day qualifiers belong on a 🚫 row, not the 🏛 row (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 2a — inside the blue box)
✅ 🚫 row — "Closed" must be capitalised: "🚫 Closed Tuesday", not "🚫 closed Tuesday" (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 3 — inside the blue box)
✅ 3+ consecutive 🏛️ rows must be consolidated to Option B format: "🏛️ Daily H:MMam - H:MMpm · … (exception qualifier)" (per Icon Order and Format.html)
✅ 🏛️ rows must use 🏛️ (U+1F3DB + U+FE0F variation selector), not bare 🏛 (U+1F3DB alone) — bare form renders inconsistently across platforms. (Icon Order and Format.html)
✅ ⏳ standalone rows must contain duration only — no prose tail after the duration value (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 4b)
✅ <img> tags have no inline style attribute
✅ <div class="stop-photos"> has no inline style attribute
✅ No <h3> inside .stop-block (use .stop-num + .stop-name spans)
✅ Every .stop-block has one .stop-num span and one .stop-name span
✅ .stop-num format is '{N}.' (digit + period), not 'Stop {N}'
✅ .stop-name span must have non-empty text content (per Stops Structure.html §3 — every stop is named after the venue)
✅ .stop-name span contains plain text only — no inner HTML tags (<a>, <em>, <span>, <br>, etc. inside the title span are format violations)
✅ Stop-title connector is `or`, never `+`
✅ Every .stop-name carries a type-modifier class (self — only valid modifier; guided retired 2026-05-20; train retired 2026-04-26)
✅ Every .stop-name carries exactly ONE type-modifier class
✅ No literal 🚩 / 🎒 / 🚆 / 🎟️ / 📅 typed into .stop-name text (CSS renders via ::before)
✅ Stop-name modifier class matches body shape (self→XOR of .tour-box containing 📍 or .ticket-box+🎟️ — never both; guided modifier retired 2026-05-20; train modifier retired 2026-04-26)
✅ No 📅 appears inside any .ticket-box (tickets lead with 🎟️, never 📅)
✅ 🎟 row must be booking link only — no text before the link (descriptions, genre labels, qualifiers belong in the stop paragraph above the box, not on the 🎟 row; caught 2026-05-08)
✅ 🎟 row must end at </a> — ( advisory text belongs on a ⚠️ row — drift: "🎟 amtrak.com · reserve a seat" 2026-05-08)
✅ 🎟 must not be used for free venues — use 🆓 instead; "🎟 Free — no booking needed" is always wrong (locked 2026-05-24)
✅ 📍 / 📖 rows must end at </a> — (address and Wikipedia link are the complete row content; per Icon Order and Format.html )
✅ 🎫 row format — must be exactly: 🎫 book at: <a>site</a> — nothing before "book at:", nothing between "book at:" and the link, nothing after </a> (global rule, 2026-05-10)
✅ No ticket-signal product (ticket / fast-track entry / hosted entry / timed-entry / admission / rooftop pass) inside any .tour-box (those rows belong in .ticket-box led by 🎟️)
✅ Every .stop-block contains a .stop-photos wrapper
✅ No .stop-block contains more than one .stop-photos wrapper
✅ Every .stop-block contains at least one 🏛️ opening-hours row
✅ No .stop-block has a 🚶 walk time > 44 min (cap is 40 min; 4 min lean applied)
✅ Global walk cap — no 🚶 time exceeds 44 min in any section (cap is 40 min; 4 min lean applied; hard fail — remove walk or use 🚕 only)
✅ Guide has at most 2 "No pictures found." stops (Photos Rules.html § 4 — harvest during research)
✅ Every .stop-photos wrapper contains exactly 1 <img> tag (or .stop-photos-empty negative-finding line)
✅ Every <img> inside .stop-photos has a non-empty alt attribute
✅ <img src> inside .stop-photos starts with "_build/assets/" (Photos Rules.html Storage — relative path)
✅ <img alt> inside .stop-photos does not start with "photo of"/"image of"/"picture of" (Photos Rules.html Alt text — "Just the subject name. No 'photo of' prefix.")
✅ <img src> filename starts with "800px-" (Photos Rules.html Harvest recipe step 6 — preserve the 800px-{Filename} thumb)
✅ .stop-photos-empty wrapper holds the literal <em>No pictures found.</em> (Photos Rules.html When Commons truly has nothing usable)
✅ Photo filenames must not match artwork/painting patterns — no paintings, illustrations, engravings, or circa-dated Wikimedia files (stop photos must be real photographs, not artwork)
✅ Photo filenames must not contain weak-filename patterns (Building, Exterior, Facade, Outside, Front_view) without a <!-- photo-ok: reason --> sign-off — building exteriors are a last resort for non-architectural stops (Photos Rules.html § 9)
✅ .stop-photos-empty wrapper must contain no <img> tag — empty wrapper holds only <em>No pictures found.</em> (Photos Rules.html § 6)
✅ No build annotations in <img alt> text — [TODO], [UPDATE], [CHECK], 🔴 etc. must be stripped before shipping (same rule as stop-name annotation leakage)
✅ No duplicate photo src filenames across stops — each stop needs its own unique photo
✅ No placeholder-photo services in <img> src (picsum/placehold/etc.)
✅ No base64 "data:image/" src in <img> (dev guide uses relative _build/assets/ paths)
✅ No city-landing tour links (viator /d\d+-ttd or /d\d+ bare, getyourguide /l\d+/)
✅ No Wikimedia hotlinks in <img> src (download to Guides/{City}/_build/assets/ and use relative path)
✅ No external hotlinks in <img> src — all photos must be local files in _build/assets/ (photos must be downloaded, not hotlinked from external sites, restaurant pages, CDNs, or any other remote source)
✅ Every <img src="_build/assets/..."> resolves to a real file on disk (Photos Rules.html Storage)
✅ Every <img src="_build/assets/..."> file is a valid image (JPEG/PNG/GIF/WebP magic-byte check, per Photos Rules.html — catches silent-download-failure drift)
✅ Every <img src="_build/assets/..."> has at least one dimension ≥ 250 px — images where max(width, height) < 250 are almost certainly download-failure placeholders (e.g. 60×60 PNG icons). Real guide photos are always much larger. Caught 2026-05-08.
✅ All guided stops have NO stop-level 📍 (meeting point lives inside each tour box)
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries its own 📍 meeting point
⚠️ 5 day(s) with fewer than 4 stops (floor: ≥4 for a full day — confirm this is an intentional half-day or Dani-approved short day)
     → "Day 1" (3 stops); "Day 2" (3 stops); "Day 3" (2 stops); "Day 5" (2 stops); "Day 6" (3 stops)
     ✏️  Add <!-- warn-ok: 5-day-s-with-fewer-than-4-stops-floor-4-for-a-full-day WHY --> in the guide to document why this is acceptable
✅ Guide must contain at least one 📅 tour-box — zero tour boxes means tour-first research was skipped entirely (Tours - Extra Section.html)
✅ Guide must contain at least one 🎟 ticket-box (skip-the-line / timed-entry), or explain absence with <!-- no-skip-the-line: reason --> (Tickets.html)
✅ .tour-box classes used correctly (Type 1 Guided leads with 📅; Type 2 Option 1 self-walk contains 📍 — last row per )
✅ .ticket-box classes used correctly (every ticket-box leads with 🎟️)
✅ Ticket rows live in .ticket-box, never in .tour-box
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries a star rating (e.g. 4.5★)
✅ Every 📅 tour-box names the booking platform (Viator / GetYourGuide / TripAdvisor / Klook)
✅ Every 📅 tour block is wrapped in <div class="tour-box"> (no bare 📅 outside a .tour-box)
✅ Every 🎟️ skip-the-line ticket row is wrapped in <div class="ticket-box"> (no bare 🎟️ outside a .ticket-box, regardless of stop type)
✅ <div class="tour-box"> has no inline style attribute
✅ tour-boxes must be flat siblings — never nested (double blue bar = missing </div> after tour-meet)
✅ Every 📅 tour-box has its tour name hyperlinked (📅 <a>Tour Name</a>)
✅ 📅 tour-box lead row has exactly one <a> link — platform name is plain text, not a hyperlink (drift: second link added for venue site, e.g. `📅 <a>Tour</a> — <a>venue.org</a> · Platform 4.5★`)
✅ 📅 lead row fully encapsulated — operator · rating · reviews inside the <a> tag (broken: `📅 <a>Name</a> · Viator · 4.7★`; correct: `📅 <a>Name · Viator · 4.7★</a>`; per Tours - Extra Section.html locked 2026-05-19)
✅ 📅 link text must end with "· N.N[★/⭐] · N+ reviews" and carry ≥2 · separators (format: Title · Operator · 4.7★ · 900+ reviews — no trailing text, no missing · before rating) (per Tours - Extra Section.html)
✅ 📅 tour name must be wrapped in <strong> inside the <a> link — bare text fails (correct: `📅 <a><strong>Tour Name</strong> · Viator · 4.7★ · 900+ reviews</a>`; per guide_v2.css locked 2026-05-19: only <strong> is bold inside .tour-box a)
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries 🕐 start time
✅ 🕐 start-time format: H:MMam or H:MMpm only — attached, lowercase, nothing else before the · separator
✅ 🕐 combined row — ⏳ and 👥 must be on the same div in order: 🕐 {H:MM am/pm} · ⏳ {duration} · 👥 {N or descriptor} (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 6a)
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries ⏳ duration
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries 👥 max group size
✅ Every 📅 tour-box carries a review count (e.g. "2,100+ reviews")
✅ Review counts round down to nearest 10 (<100) or 100 (≥100) and end in "+ reviews"
✅ No currency symbols in .tour-box — prices do not belong in the guide ($, €, £, ¥)
✅ Every stop has distinct booking URLs across its tour-boxes (no copy-paste duplicates)
✅ Tour-boxes with a shared 📍 address carry <!-- shared-address-ok: reason --> sentinel
✅ No 📖 Wikipedia link inside a .tour-box (📖 is a stop-level element)
✅ No 📒 stop-summary inside a .tour-box (📒 is a stop-level element)
✅ No .stop-photos wrapper inside a .tour-box (photos come AFTER all tour-boxes)
✅ No .stop-photos wrapper inside a .ticket-box (Photos Rules.html Placement — photos belong directly under .stop-block, never inside .ticket-box)
✅ Photo block (.stop-photos / .stop-photos-empty) is the LAST element inside .stop-block (Photos Rules.html Placement)
✅ 📍 address is the LAST row of every .tour-box / .ticket-box (per CORE RULES/Stops Structure.html — Type 2 Option 1, Type 2 Option 2, Type 3 ticket box. Type 1 📅 tour-boxes carry the meeting point inside .tour-meet, exempt.)
✅ Universal stop-box row order — inside every .ticket-box and self-walk .tour-box: 🚐 → 🏛/⏳ → 🚫 → ⏰/🕐 → 🆓/💵 → ⚠️ → 📍 (per Icon Order and Format.html universal row order)
✅ Universal stop-box mutual exclusion — 🏛 OR ⏳ (not both), ⏰ OR 🕐 (not both), 🆓 OR 💵 (not both) inside any single box (per Icon Order and Format.html — mutually exclusive pairs)
✅ Venue days fully covered — 🏛 (open days+hours) + 🚫 (closed days) together must account for all 7 days of the week; no day may be missing or listed on both sides
✅ Motion Rule — every motion row matches a valid pattern: 🚶 N · 🚕 M  or  🚕 M  or tram/metro pattern. Anything else fails.
✅ No two consecutive motion rows in the same box — 🚶 and 🚕 must share one row ("🚶 N min · 🚕 M min"); splitting them into adjacent <div> rows is format drift (Motion Rule)
✅ 🚐 never in motion banners (.next / .next-tram / .hotel-first / .arrive-first) — emoji belongs to tour operator only; use 🚕 / 🚶 / 🚎 / 🚝 / 🚢 for motion (per Tours - Extra Section.html )
✅ Information rows are plain text — no embedded <a> in 🏛 / ⏰ / 🆓 / 🚫 / 💵 / ⚠️ rows (per CORE RULES/Stops Structure.html — supplementary booking info goes on its own row or its own box, never spliced inline into an information row.)
✅ ⏰ rows are duration-only — valid: "⏰ ~Nh", "⏰ ~N.Nh", "⏰ ~N min", "⏰ ~Nh N min" (~ prefix required · no ranges · nothing else on row · min allowed for sub-hour visits, mixed Nh N min for long stops) (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 4b — inside the blue box)
✅ 🚫 rows must be exactly "🚫 Closed {Full weekday(s)}" — full day names only (no abbreviations), no extra text (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 3 — inside the blue box)
✅ 🆓 rows must be exactly "🆓 Free" — nothing else (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 5a — inside the blue box)
✅ 💵 rows must be exactly "💵 Cash Only" — nothing else (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 5b — inside the blue box)
✅ ⚠️ rows must have non-empty warning text after the icon — bare ⚠️ is a fail (per Icon Order and Format.html Pos 6 — inside the blue box)
✅ 📅 rows must contain " · " separator — format: 📅 {Tour Title} · {Operator} (drift guard: guided-tour format retired 2026-05-20; 📅 rows should not appear in new guides — no · means operator was dropped or old format leaked)
✅ Time durations use English format, not clock notation (correct: "2 hrs", "1 hr", "1 hr 25 min"; wrong: "2h00", "1h25") 
✅ 📅 rows must use " · " between tour name and operator — no em-dash (correct: 📅 [Tour] · Operator · 4.5★; wrong: 📅 [Tour] — Operator · 4.5★)
✅ 📅 row format: tour title link must immediately follow icon — nothing between 📅 and <a href="..."> (drift guard: guided-tour format retired 2026-05-20; format is 📅 <a>Tour Title</a> · Operator)
✅ Food-section review links must have link text "N.N⭐ · N+ reviews" (e.g. <a href="...">4.6⭐ · 2000+ reviews</a>) — tight star (no space before ⭐), no extra text, must use ⭐ (not ★), must include + and "reviews" (Cappuccino / Restaurants Near Hotel / Downtown - Extra Section rules)
✅ Food-section review link (class="review-link") must point to Yelp, Google Reviews, or Local Guide — not the venue's own site, not Viator, not TripAdvisor. Per Cappuccino § 3 / Restaurants Near Hotel § 4b / Downtown § 5 (locked 2026-05-24)
✅ Food-section rating link (N.N⭐ · N+ reviews) in .extras-sub must have class="review-link" — without it .extras-sub a { color: inherit; font-weight: inherit } renders the link dark+bold instead of blue (#2867c4) + normal weight (guide_v2.css § .extras-sub a.review-link; Cappuccino / RNH / Downtown — locked 2026-05-26)
✅ class="review-link" anchor must not contain <strong> — <strong> overrides font-weight:normal set by .extras-sub a.review-link and makes the rating bold. Plain text only inside the review-link anchor (guide_v2.css § .extras-sub a.review-link — locked 2026-05-26)
✅ GLOBAL — rating tokens are tight: a decimal rating sits flush against its star (N.N⭐), never with a space before ⭐ (N.N ⭐). Per Dani 2026-05-20 — newest rule prevails over the retired 2026-05-19 spaced form.
✅ 🎟 ticket-box lead row must include star rating — format: 🎟 {Ticket Title} · {N.N⭐} · {platform} (per Tickets.html § 2 — no parentheses around the rating)
✅ 🎟 ticket-box platform links (Viator / GetYourGuide / TripAdvisor / Klook) must include review count — format: 🎟 {Title} · {N.N⭐} · {N}+ reviews · {Platform} (per Tickets.html §2; venue-site last-resort links are exempt)
✅ No <br> inside any logistics box (.tour-box / .ticket-box / .shows-box / .entry-body / .transit-box) — every row must be its own <div> (old <br>-separated format is retired)
✅ Day-trip and logistics boxes use emoji-led <div> rows — no text-label prefixes ("Why:", "Train:", "Getting there:", "Book via:") starting a row inside any box (per Day Trips format — Why description is a plain <div> inside the transit-box; transport on 🚊/🚄/🚕/🚐 row; booking on 🎟️/🎫 row; "book at:" mid-row in 🎫 is allowed)
✅ Every .day-block opens with `🏨 FROM HOTEL:` banner (per Day Structure.html — bookends are mandatory)
✅ Every .day-block ends with `→ hotel` closer banner (per Day Structure.html — last element of the day-block)
✅ `→ hotel` closer row must be exactly "🚶 {N} · 🚕 {N} → hotel" — starts with 🚶, has 🚕 separated by · , ends with → hotel, nothing else (per Icon Order and Format.html ). Train Day return-to-hotel hop is `🚉 ARRIVE {home station}: 🚶 N · 🚕 M → hotel` in an .arrive-first div (per Stops Structure.html).
✅ Every .day-block starts stop numbering at 1 and runs consecutively (per Day Structure.html — stop count resets per day, no cross-day bleed)
✅ .day-header matches one of the three locked patterns (per Day Structure.html — `Day N` / `Day N — Train Day — {Destination}` / `Day N — Guided Coach to {Destination}`)
✅ No .leave-first divs — the 🚊 LEAVE banner concept was removed 2026-05-26; delete any remaining .leave-first divs from the guide
✅ `🏨 FROM HOTEL:` banner uses uppercase HOTEL (per Hotel Banner.html Hotel naming rule — HOTEL uppercase in banners)
✅ 🏨 FROM HOTEL: line must not contain a departure time (Rule 402 — time after FROM HOTEL: is drift; use transit info only)
✅ Every consecutive pair of stops has a transit banner (.next) between them (Motion Rule.html Stops pattern — one banner per stop transition, none may be skipped)
✅ 🏨 FROM HOTEL: banner appears exactly once per day-block — more than one means two days were accidentally merged (Day Structure.html §2)
✅ Day-block id="dayN" matches the Day N number in the header — mismatch breaks anchor navigation (copy-paste error)
✅ No duplicate stop names within the same day-block — repeated name means a stop was copy-pasted and not updated
✅ Train Day — every Train Day must carry a 🎫 book at: [Booking Operator] row (Day Structure.html §7)
✅ Train Day — a blank line is required in source between the 🎫 booking row and <div class="train"> (guide_v2.css margin-top provides the visual gap; the blank line enforces the structural boundary in source)
✅ Train Day — timetable rows (.train-time) must be wrapped in <div class="train"> (.train-header sits ABOVE div.train as a sibling; only .train-time rows go inside) (guide_v2.css div.train .train-time — unwrapped timetable renders unstyled: no blue bg, no indented rows)
✅ Train Day — every 🚊/🚄 train-header must carry a 🎫 book at: [Train Ticket Operator] row between the header and the timetable (div.train) — applies to both outbound and return blocks (Stops Structure.html §5)
✅ Day numbers are sequential with no gaps and no duplicates — Day 1, Day 2, Day 3 … (Day Structure.html §4)
✅ Day-header text contains no build annotations — [UPDATE], [CHECK], 🔴, [TBD] etc. must be stripped before shipping
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — no national holidays / calendar dates (per Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html + cleanliness Rule 175 — "recurring weekly patterns only; no national holidays")
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — every entry matches `{Category} · Closed {Day}` (per Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html What each entry looks like)
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — bold only the category name (per Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html — "Don't bold the day or anything else on the line")
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — when zero entries ship, the section carries the literal "No notable city-wide weekly closures in {City}." negative-finding line (per Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html When the destination has no notable pattern)
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — day at the end of each entry is a valid weekday (Monday-Sunday, singular or plural)
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — each venue appears exactly once (combine all closure days into one entry per venue; no duplicate rows for the same venue)
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — entries sharing the same closure day must be consolidated into one entry (per Weekly Closures - Extra Section.html § 2 examples — same-day categories are always grouped)
✅ 🗓️ Weekly Closures — no blank lines between .stop-row elements (blank lines create visual spacing gaps; rows must be adjacent in source HTML)
